        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-12-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="261"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <head>261. Memorandum From the Deputy Secretary of Defense (<persName
                        corresp="#p_QDA1" type="from">Quarles</persName>) to the Secretary of the
                    Army (<persName type="to">Brucker</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d261fn1">Source: Washington National Records Center, <gloss
                            target="#t_OASDISA1">OASD/ISA</gloss> Files: FRC 61 B 1672, 471.6 Korea.
                        Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-12-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1957</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Introduction into Korea of the Honest <persName>John</persName> and 280mm
                        Gun, [<hi rend="italic">1 line of source text not declassified</hi>] (Top
                        Secret)</item>
                </list>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_YCYD1">You</persName> hereby are authorized, in
                    implementation of State–Defense cables (1) To Seoul 229, dtd Sept 16, 1957;<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d261fn2">
                        <ref target="#d247">Document 247</ref>.</note> (2) <gloss target="#t_Def1"
                        >DEF</gloss> 933850, dtd Dec <pb facs="0561" n="533" xml:id="pg_533"/> 11,
                        1957;<note n="3" xml:id="d261fn3">
                        <ref target="#d257">Document 257</ref>.</note> (3) <gloss target="#t_Def1"
                        >DEF</gloss> 933889, dtd Dec 11, 1957,<note n="4" xml:id="d261fn4">Not
                        found.</note> to introduce into Korea the Honest <persName>John</persName>
                    and 280mm gun, [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line of source text not
                        declassified</hi>] as soon as is feasible under Army deployment
                    schedules.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_QDA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Donald A. Quarles</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="5" xml:id="d261fn5">Printed from a copy that bears this stamped
                            signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
